Brazil Government Studying Increase in Oil Taxes, Valor Reports

-- B y   P e t e r   M i l l a r d
-- 
2011-09-02T11:44:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/brazil-government-studying-increase-in-oil-taxes-valor-reports.html
Brazil ’s government is studying an
increase of a special participation tax on oil production that
may raise revenue by 3 billion reais ($1.85 billion), Valor
Economico reported, without saying where it got the information.  The tax increase would benefit states that don’t produce
any oil and help resolve a debate in Congress over how to
distribute royalties between producing and non-producing states,
the Sao Paulo-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Millard in Rio de Janeiro at 
 pmillard1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jessica Brice at 
 jbrice1@bloomberg.net  